The history of discovering of folklore by the European thought, collecting of
folklore in Russia, the general problems of folklore-studies (folklore and a myth,
folklore and the literature, a problem of chronology and area variabilities in
folklore) are described in the course. Both the review of the basic types/genres
of Russian folklore, and the description of calendar cycles are given. The pactical
part of the course is devoted to the analysis of folklore/postfolklore texts of
different genres.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The basic purpose of the course is to give the notice about specificity of Russian folklore and
postfolklore, their basic types, genres and cycles.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course the student 1) has the general knowledge about the specificity of folklore; 2) gets acquainted with history of Russian folklore-studies; 3) has notion about the basic genres of Russian traditional folklore; 4) understands calendar cycles of Russian folklore; 5) knows about postfolklore in Russia and its basic genres.
